bib_record.title: Isotopically resolved neutron total cross sections at intermediate energies

free_txt: Neutron Research facility of the Los Alamos Neutron
All detectors - flux monitor, veto detector
and TOF detector consisted of BC-400 fast
scintillation plastic detectors with PMT readout. Flux
monitor and veto detector had scintillator thickness
of 0.25 inches. TOF detector had thickness of 1 inch.
Neutron Research facility of the Los Alamos Neutron
Neutrons are produced by spallation reaction.
protons with energy of 800 MeV bombard water cooled
7.5 cm long tungsten target. Permanent magnet deflects
all generated charged particles from the beam
Measurement was performed at the beamline 15R.
Proton macropulses are delivered to the tungsten
target at 120Hz. Each macropulse consists of cca 350
micropulses spaced 1.8 mu-s apart. Neutron beam was
collimated using steel collimator with total thickness
of 24 inches. After collimation, the beam passed
through a flux monitor, the sample, a veto detector,
and the time-of-flight detector approximately 25m from
the neutron source. Neutron energy was determined by
time of flight. Total cross sections were determined
